               <p>CHARLES JOHN BYTHESEA BROME. I am in no business. On the 25th of July I was in <placeName id="t18320906-136-crimeloc771">St. James's Park</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-136-crimeloc771" type="placeName" value="St. James's Park"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-136-crimeloc771" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-136-off769 t18320906-136-crimeloc771"></join>, coming from Downing-street - I saw two men and a boy running into the Tilt-yard; they got out of sight - some person said they had picked my pocket - I ran into the Tilt-yard, and inquired which way they had run - when I got to the Horse Guards, I saw them again; they saw me, and set off running - the prisoner dropped my purse, which I took up; I pursued and caught him, and then came back for my purse - this is it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was running through the passage, and saw the purse on the ground; I took it up.</p>
               <p>
